      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Exciting gelding VERBICI (7) stretched his unbeaten run to three with a dominant performance in the Nutrien final at Wagga last start, settling back in the field before surging home to cruise in by 14m. Cops his widest draw yet but the form is impossible to knock. KYVALLEY DIABLO (6) looked promising in kicking off his career with a 9m win at Bendigo. Recovered from an early break there so still has something to learn but easily won a trial since and that should have brought him on. Draws inside the favourite so could challenge him. CHIEF KENNY (5) has yet to win but continues to race well, finishing runner-up in five of his six starts. Can be competitive again. SUMMER KISS (3) showed some improvement to place at start number two and draws well as does SUMTHIN DIFFERENT (2) who broke last time but did produce a couple of handy results early on.",
